!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

recover /rɪˈkʌvə/

(recovering,recovered,recovers) 

1. V-I When you recover from an illness or an injury, you become well again. 痊愈; 恢复健康 

例： He is recovering from a knee injury. 他的膝伤正在痊愈。 

2. V-I If you recover from an unhappy or unpleasant experience, you stop being upset by it. (从不愉快的经历中) 恢复 

例： ...a tragedy from which he never fully recovered. …一场他再也没有完全从中恢复过来的悲剧。 

3. V-I If something recovers from a period of weakness or difficulty, it improves or gets stronger again. (从弱势或困境中) 好转 

例： He recovered from a 4-2 deficit to reach the quarter-finals. 他从4－2的失利中恢复过来，进入1/4决赛。 

4. V-T If you recover something that has been lost or stolen, you find it or get it back. 重新找回 

例： Police raided five houses in Brooklyn and recovered stolen goods. 警察突击搜查了位于布鲁克林的5栋住宅，找回了被盗物品。 

5. V-T If you recover a mental or physical state, it comes back again. For example, if you recover consciousness, you become conscious again. 恢复 (身心状态或意识) 

例： She had a severe attack of asthma and it took an hour to recover her breath. 她犯了一次严重的哮喘，一个小时之后才恢复正常呼吸。 

6. V-T If you recover money that you have spent, invested, or lent to someone, you get the same amount back. 收回 (花掉、投资或借出的钱) 

例： Legal action is being taken to recover the money. 正采取法律措施来收回那笔钱。

